UID:cht-emerging-voices-ai-society-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260724T115115Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: Center for Humane Technology: Emerging Voices in AI and S
 ociety Fellowship (Inaugural Cohort)
DESCRIPTION:CHT's inaugural Emerging Voices in AI and Society Fellowship pl
 aces 3 fellows (one per focus area) in a 6-month\, part-time program to de
 velop rigorous public-impact research and writing on how AI is reshaping s
 ociety. Fellows choose from 5 focus areas: (1) AI and Cognition — what A
 I does to human judgment\, critical thinking\, and intellectual independen
 ce\; (2) AI and Relationships — AI's effects on intimacy\, companionship
 \, and social bonds\; (3) AI and Surveillance — how AI enables monitorin
 g\, tracking\, and control\; (4) AI and Spirituality — AI's intersection
  with meaning\, transcendence\, and religious practice\; (5) Inside the Ma
 chine: AI From a Technologist's Perspective. Up to 2 focus areas per appli
 cation. DELIVERABLES: one flagship research piece\, report\, or long-form 
 essay for public impact\; 1-3 op-eds (placed in target outlets or CHT Subs
 tack)\; one podcast appearance (Your Undivided Attention or equivalent)\; 
 cohort meetings and bi-weekly check-ins. SUPPORT: bi-weekly guidance from 
 Senior Director of Strategy and Impact\; editorial\, communications and gr
 aphic design support\; media training and PR placement support\; CHT email
  address and Slack access\; listing on CHT's public fellows page. WHO SHOU
 LD APPLY: mid-career researchers (psychology\, sociology\, philosophy\, co
 gnitive science\, communications\, STS)\, policy analysts\, journalists co
 vering tech and society\, civil society advocates\, or technologists with 
 insider perspective. Strong preference for those with a public writing tra
 ck record (op-eds\, Substack\, peer-reviewed work) and some public presenc
 e. HOW TO APPLY: 1-2 page research proposal per topic (up to 2)\, CV/resum
 e (2 pages max)\, 2-minute video explaining fit\, writing sample. Deadline
 : Sunday 12 July 2026\, 11:59pm EST.\n\nOrganisation: Center for Humane Te
 chnology (CHT)\nLocation: Remote\, 10 hours/week overlapping with EST requ
 ired.\nAward: $30\,000 fixed stipend paid in three milestone-based tranche
 s. No application fee.\nDuration: 6 months: September 14\, 2026 through Ma
 rch 18\, 2027. 15 hours per week.\n\nMore: https://www.humanetech.com/fell
 owship?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.humanetech.com/fellowship?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrant
 desk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote\, 10 hours/week overlapping with EST required.
END:VEVENT
